<TITLE> Chittagong courthouse construction to finish by 2009: adviser </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Jan 26 (bdnews24.com)  Construction of the new Chittagong courthouse will be completed by 2009, housing and public works adviser Ghulam Quader said Saturday. The new courthouse costing Tk 47 crore will accommodate 60 courtrooms, a bank, a post office and ample space for support staff, the adviser told reporters. The new courthouse will also contain six elevators and other modern conveniences. The current century-old Chittagong courthouse will be completely renovated for use, keeping its infrastructure intact, Quader also told reporters while on an inspection of the ongoing renovation of the courthouse. The construction of the new courthouse started in 1998, along with the repair and preservation work of the old, is set to be completed by the end of 2009, according to Quazi Golam Mortuza, an engineer under the Public Works Department. He informed the adviser that following the completion of the new courthouse, the judges' block could be transferred into the new building. The adviser also told reporters that the government would take proper measures to ensure that the court continues to function through the renovation, relocation and construction process, and that all obstacles to timely completion of construction are removed. Among those accompanying the adviser during the inspection were Chittagong divisional commissioner Hossain Jamil and deputy commissioner Ashraf Shamim. bdnews2
